# Virar Stationery & Jumbo Xerox — AI System Rules

You are an AI assistant helping to build a world-class, high-performance website for a local stationery and printing business.
This codebase is highly optimized for AI consumption.

## Core Directives
1. **NO FRAMEWORKS**: This project uses strict Vanilla JS (ES6 modules), native CSS, and Bootstrap 5. Do not propose React, Vue, Tailwind, or bundlers (Vite/Webpack) unless explicitly instructed by the user.
2. **MAINTAIN ARCHITECTURE**: Do not dump code into the root directory. Follow the strict folder structure defined below.
3. **DO NOT READ `style.css` FULLY**: `assets/css/style.css` is massive (~8,400 lines). NEVER read the whole file. Instead, read the Table of Contents at the top of the file, and use `grep` to find the exact `/* === SECTION: [NAME] === */` marker before viewing or editing that specific block.

## Architecture Map
- `index.html` → The main single-page application entry point.
- `pages/` → Contains secondary pages (`privacy.html`, `terms.html`, `sitemap.html`).
- `assets/images/brand/` → Core logos and main UI imagery.
- `assets/images/products/` → Images of specific stationery products.
- `assets/images/gallery/` → Photos of the shop interior and equipment.
- `assets/css/style.css` → Global master stylesheet. (See TOC inside).
- `assets/css/pages/` → Stylesheets specific to secondary pages.
- `assets/js/main.js` → The primary orchestrator. Imports all modules.
- `assets/js/config.js` → Global frozen constants (phone numbers, API keys).
- `assets/js/data/business-data.js` → Central source of truth for services and pricing.
- `assets/js/utils/` → Helper functions (e.g. WhatsApp URL generation).
- `assets/js/features/` → Isolated vanilla JS feature modules.
- `docs/` → Contains deep architectural context (`AI_CONTEXT.md`, `DIRECTORY_MAP.md`).

## Safe Execution Pattern
Every JavaScript feature must be isolated and initialized using the `safeRun` utility inside `main.js`. If one feature crashes, the rest of the application must continue to function.

## Tone & Output
- Be extremely concise.
- Output high-quality, production-ready code.
- If writing a new CSS rule, place it in the appropriate `/* === SECTION === */` inside `style.css`.
